snippet.textDisplay: I used to kick arse playing COD: Warzone on PS4 with a Nacon Revolution Pro controller, even against PC players. Now I have a PC so I use keyboard and mouse. I used to game on PC back in the day so it didn't take long to get back into it. In some ways I still prefer the controller. The mouse is nice and I like that you can turn around in a fraction of a second and I am good enough to still kick arse most of the time but I'm not sure I'm as good as I was on a controller. On the other hand, literally, the keyboard controls are garbage compared to a controller. It's so awkward reaching for random buttons to use equipment, killstreaks etc, having your hand in this awkward claw position and only being able to move at full speed or not at all is a massive downgrade compared to ergonomics and movement with a joystick. I have been looking at the gaming keypad devices that are becoming more popular so that I can use a mouse with the right hand and a keypad/joystick with the left hand. I think that would be the sweet spot for gaming.
